Deprecated API

Contents
  • Deprecated Interfaces
  • Deprecated Classes
  • Deprecated Fields
  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Constructors
Deprecated Interfaces
com.jidesoft.swing.JideMenu.MenuCreator
          The createMenu method of MenuCreator should JPopupMenu as parameter. Since it's a public API we have to deprecated this one and ask users to use JideMenu.PopupMenuCustomizer instead. 
 

Deprecated Classes
com.jidesoft.swing.ButtonPanel
          replaced by ButtonPanel under com.jidesoft.dialog. 
 

Deprecated Fields
com.jidesoft.plaf.LookAndFeelFactory.JIDE_STYLE
          JIDE_STYLE name is confusing because people think this is a special style such as VSNET_STYLE or OFFICE2003_STYLE. So we decided to rename it to LookAndFeelFactory.JIDE_STYLE_INSTALLED. If you used this before, please change it to use JIDE_STYLE_INSTALLED instead. 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideButton.PROPERTY_ORIENTATION_CHANGED
          use PROPERTY_ORIENTATION instead. The string values of both constants are the same. 
 

Deprecated Methods
com.jidesoft.icons.ColorFilter.createDimmedImage(Image)
          the name is wrong. Replaced by createBrighterImage(). 
com.jidesoft.popup.JidePopup.createPopupContainer()
          use JidePopup.createHeavyweightPopupContainer(java.awt.Component) instead. 
com.jidesoft.popup.JidePopup.createPopupContainer(Component)
          use JidePopup.createHeavyweightPopupContainer(java.awt.Component) instead. 
com.jidesoft.dialog.BannerPanel.getImageLabel()
          use BannerPanel.getIconComponent() instead. We also add a setter for it which was missing before. 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideMenu.getMenuCreator()
          useJideMenu.PopupMenuCustomizer and JideMenu.getPopupMenuCustomizer() instead. 
com.jidesoft.swing.CheckBoxList.getSelectedObjects()
          We keep this method in order to be compatible with CheckBoxListWithSelectable. You should use CheckBoxList.getCheckBoxListSelectedValues() instead. Or you can use CheckBoxList.getCheckBoxListSelectionModel() to get the selection model and get the selected indices from there. 
com.jidesoft.grouper.ObjectGrouperManager.getValue(Object, Class, GrouperContext)
          the method is changed to ObjectGrouperManager.getGroupValue(Object,Class,GrouperContext). 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideSwingUtilities.getWindow(Component)
          Please use JideSwingUtilities.getWindowForComponent(java.awt.Component) instead. getWindowForComponent method is the same as the same name method in JOptionPane. We have to copy it here because it's not public. getWindowForComponent is better than this method is because it will give you a shared root frame even when parentComponent is null. You can refer to JOptionPane.getRootFrame() for more information. 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideTabbedPane.isBoxStyleTab()
          As JideTabbedPane can now support many different style, box style is just one of them. So this is method is replaced by JideTabbedPane.getTabShape() method. If the return value is STYLE_BOX, it is a box style tab. 
com.jidesoft.utils.SystemInfo.isJdk16Above()
          use SystemInfo.isJdk6Above(). Nothing is wrong with this method. It's just Sun starts to call JDK1.6 as JDK6 now. 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideTabbedPane.isShrinkTabs()
          Since we added more tab resize option, shrinkTabs is just one of those. You can call JideTabbedPane.getTabResizeMode(). If the value is JideTabbedPane.RESIZE_MODE_FIT, it means shrinkTabs is true. Otherwise, it's false. 
com.jidesoft.swing.TreeSearchable.populateTreePathes()
          spell error. Use TreeSearchable.populateTreePaths() instead. 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideTabbedPane.setBoxStyleTab(boolean)
          As JideTabbedPane can now support many different style, box style is just one of them. So a better way is to change style using JideTabbedPane.setTabShape(int) method. 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideMenu.setMenuCreator(JideMenu.MenuCreator)
          useJideMenu.PopupMenuCustomizer and JideMenu.setPopupMenuCustomizer(com.jidesoft.swing.JideMenu.PopupMenuCustomizer) instead. 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideTabbedPane.setShrinkTabs(boolean)
          Since we added more tab resize option, shrinkTabs is just one of those. You can call JideTabbedPane.setTabResizeMode(int) and set to JideTabbedPane.RESIZE_MODE_FIT which is equavilent to setShrinkTabs(true). JideTabbedPane.RESIZE_MODE_NONE is equavilent to setShrinkTabs(false). 
com.jidesoft.swing.StyledLabel.setStyleRange(StyleRange)
          use StyledLabel.addStyleRange(StyleRange) instead. The method name "set" usually means clear all previous style range and set this as the new one, which is not correct. So using method name "add" makes more sense. 
com.jidesoft.dialog.StandardDialog.show()
          As of JDK version 1.5, replaced by Component.setVisible(boolean). 
com.jidesoft.swing.JideSwingUtilities.synchonizeView(JViewport, JViewport, int)
          there is a typo. Use JideSwingUtilities.synchronizeView(javax.swing.JViewport,javax.swing.JViewport,int). 
com.jidesoft.utils.PortingUtils.withinScreen(Component, Point)
          Please use PortingUtils.ensureOnScreen(java.awt.Rectangle) instead. 
 

Deprecated Constructors
com.jidesoft.icons.ColorFilter(boolean, int)
          use getInstance instead to reuse the same instance 
com.jidesoft.icons.MaskFilter(Color, Color)
          use getInstance instead to reuse the same instance
